.TH getpagesize 2
.SH NAME
\*Lgetpagesize\*O \- Gets the system page size
.SH SYNOPSIS 
.sS
.PP
\*Lint getpagesize ( void );
.sE 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "getpagesize function"
.iX "system page size" "returning"
.iX "page size" "system versus hardware"
.PP
The \*Lgetpagesize(\|)\*O function returns the number of bytes
in a page.
Knowing the system page size is useful for specifying arguments to
memory management system calls.
.PP
The page size is a system page size and may not be the
same as the underlying hardware page size.
.SH RETURN VALUES
The
\*Lgetpagesize(\|)\*O
function returns the number of bytes in a page, and is always
successful.
